======================================================================
RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN det(I+A) AND F_p
======================================================================

  det(I+A) = (p+1)^{(p+1)/2} / 2^p  (EXACT)
  F_p = φ^p / √5 + O(1)  (asymptotic)

  Ratio det/F_p grows like:
    ((p+1)/4)^{m} / φ^p ~ ((p+1)/4)^{(p-1)/2} / φ^p
  Since (p+1)/4 > φ² = (3+√5)/2 ≈ 2.618 for p ≥ 11:
    det(I+A) grows FASTER than F_p

  SO: F_p does NOT equal det(I+A) for Paley tournaments.
  F_p comes from the GLMY path homology, a different invariant.
  The det(I+A) formula is a SPECTRAL invariant (Gauss sums).
  F_p is a TOPOLOGICAL invariant (path homology).

  DEEP QUESTION: What is the relationship between these two?
  log(F_p) ≈ p·logφ  (topological)
  log(det(I+A)) ≈ (p/2)·log(p/4)  (spectral)
  Ratio: spectral/topological → (1/(2logφ))·log(p/4) → ∞

  But per EIGENSPACE:
  Each k≠0 eigenspace contributes log(1+Q_k) to log(F_p)
  and log|(1+λ_k)²| = log((p+1)/4) to log(det(I+A))
  So: log(det contribution)/log(F_p contribution) for each eigenspace
  P_7: spectral/eig = 0.6931, topo/eig = 0.8550, ratio = 0.8107
  P_11: spectral/eig = 1.0986, topo/eig = 0.8977, ratio = 1.2238
  P_19: spectral/eig = 1.6094, topo/eig = 0.9265, ratio = 1.7372
